<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="607" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Taylor</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-10-30"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                1896</hi></date>. (Received November 13.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 591.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your No. 589, of the 15th instant, relative to the
                            prohibition which was placed on the shipment of 307 bales of tobacco, by
                            Mr. Louis Wertheimer, from Cuba to the United States, and to inform you
                            that the case has been duly presented to the Spanish Government.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hannis Taylor.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>